oreferrer\">Lazy, composable, and modular JavaScript</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://fr.umio.us/why-ramda/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Why Ramda</a> – Introduction to the principles of ramda.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://robotlolita.me/2013/12/08/a-monad-in-practicality-first-class-failures.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">A Monad in Practicality: First-Class Failures</a> – Introduction to Either.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://robotlolita.me/2014/03/20/a-monad-in-practicality-controlling-time.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">A Monad in Practicality: Controlling Time</a> – Introduction to Futures.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/stoeffel/awesome-fp-js/blob/master/jrsinclair.com/articles/2016/gentle-introduction-to-functional-javascript-intro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">A gentle introduction to functional JavaScript</a> – A four-part series introduction functional programming in JavaScript.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://glebbahmutov.com/blog/tags/functional/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Functional programming</a> – Many articles on various aspects of functional programming in JavaScript by Gleb Bahmutov.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/hemanth/functional-programming-jargon\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Functional Programming Jargon</a> – Jargon from the functional programming world explained in JavaScript.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"httpsblogduyetnet201604awesome-functional-programming-in-javascripthtmlvideosvideos\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#httpsblogduyetnet201604awesome-functional-programming-in-javascripthtmlvideosvideos\" aria-label=\"httpsblogduyetnet201604awesome functional programming in javascripthtmlvideosvideos permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"e